// devDependencies are used when you work in your project
// Dependencies are thouse used when you are in production

Commands:
command + shift + p ==> open browser
command + , ==> open settings
control + ` ==> open terminal
npm run lint -- --fix ==> fix problems with ESlint automatically
(el primer doble -- sirve para salir de npm, porque npm no tiene fix, es Eslint que le tiene fix command)
npm run lint -- --debug ==> see more comments about errors at Eslint
npm audit fix ==> fix automatically the vulnerabilities

** command -D es por development dependencies not production dependencies **

What is a bundler?
A module bundler is a tool that takes pieces of JavaScript and their dependencies and bundles them into a single file, usually for use in the browser. You may have used tools such as Browserify, Webpack, Rollup or one of many others.

Parcel is the bundler of this project. Take your code and then it's repacking in such a way that is
generally applicable to the browsers that you are targeting.

Function components:
const Details = () => { return (<h2>Hello</h2>); };
export default Details;

Class components:
You cannot use useState, useEffect, etc

